# Wireshark Fundamentals: Capture, Filtering & Timing Analysis

This lab is a first look at Wireshark: capturing live traffic, applying a display filter, and reading the timing and addressing information Wireshark reports for a simple HTTP request/response exchange.

**1. Name three different protocols that appear in the packet listing before any filter is applied.**

`HTTP`, `TCP`, and `TLS v1.2` were all visible in the unfiltered capture.

**2. How much time elapsed from when the HTTP GET message was sent until the HTTP OK reply was received?**

- GET packet (#201) — Time = 6.726634800
- HTTP/1.1 200 OK packet (#204) — Time = 6.788712600

`6.788712600 − 6.726634800 = 0.0620778 seconds`

**3. What is the IP address of your computer? What is the IP address of the destination (gaia.cs.umass.edu)?**

- My computer — `192.168.1.137`
- gaia.cs.umass.edu — `128.119.245.12`

